# Force LF on checkout on every platform (crlfcheckout, C.1.3.2).
# Without this, Windows core.autocrlf rewrites line endings on checkout, so the
# working tree differs from the LF-committed blobs — which blocks `git checkout <tag>`
# (perpetually "dirty" tree) and corrupts byte-exact artifacts (e.g. the adapter
# bundle SHA when copied from the working tree). With this, every checkout is
# byte-identical to the commit, so canonical SHAs and clone-script checkouts hold.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.mjs text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.go text eol=lf
dist/aifs-exec.bundle.js text eol=lf
*.exe binary
*.dll binary
*.zip binary
